# Aurora — a different engine

AWS's own engine — **MySQL / PostgreSQL wire**, **rebuilt storage + replication**. ~**5× RDS MySQL / 3× RDS PostgreSQL**.

## The shared cluster volume

**Separates compute from storage.** Primary + replicas share one distributed log-structured volume:

- **6 copies across 3 AZs** (2 per AZ), writes ack on a **4-of-6 quorum**
- Replicas read the same volume → tiny lag; a new replica adds **no storage**

## Endpoints (each routes differently)

- **Cluster (writer)** → current primary (writes)
- **Reader** → load-balanced across replicas (reads)
- **Custom** → a subset (e.g. report boxes) · **Instance** → one node

On failover, **writer + reader endpoints auto-update** — the app never tracks the writer.
